  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 300 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the lamb, olive oil, onion, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Transfer the lamb mixture to a tagine or a large Dutch oven with a tight-fitting lid.",
    "Add the rehydrated fernbrake-gosari to the tagine, stirring to combine.",
    "Cover the tagine and roast for 2 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Remove the tagine from the oven and let it cool for 10 minutes.",
    "Serve the lamb and sauce over cauliflower rice or roasted vegetables."
  ],
